post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_27802605_27802667_0": {"length": 6, "quality": 0.75, "section_id": 3222}, "so_27802605_27802667_1": {"length": 20, "quality": 0.9090909090909091, "section_id": 3222}}, "n3337": {"so_27802605_27802667_0": {"length": 6, "quality": 0.75, "section_id": 3096}, "so_27802605_27802667_1": {"length": 21, "quality": 0.9545454545454546, "section_id": 3096}}, "n4659": {"so_27802605_27802667_0": {"length": 6, "quality": 0.75, "section_id": 3979}, "so_27802605_27802667_1": {"length": 20, "quality": 0.9090909090909091, "section_id": 3979}}}, "27802667": {"Id": "27802667", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>It's not allowed.</p>\n<p>In the words of the standard:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_27802605_27802667_0\">C++11 8.3.2/5: A reference shall be initialized to refer to a valid object or function.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>However, it's not something that the compiler can, in general, diagnose, since the validity of a pointer is a run-time thing. So there's no requirement to diagnose the error, and probably no compiler warning, just undefined behaviour.</p>\n<p>The standard specifically mentions this case:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_27802605_27802667_1\"><em>Note:</em> in particular, a null reference cannot exist in a well-defined program, because the only way to create such a reference would be to bind it to the \u201cobject\u201d obtained by dereferencing a null pointer, which causes undefined behavior.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "204847", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-06T16:20:46.160", "Score": "14", "CreationDate": "2015-01-06T16:15:46.123", "ParentId": "27802605", "CommentCount": "3", "LastEditDate": "2015-01-06T16:20:46.160", "OwnerUserId": "204847"}, "27802605": {"ViewCount": "113", "Body": "<pre><code>int *ptr = 0;\nint &amp;ref = *ptr;\n</code></pre>\n<p>I write above code in Visual Studio and it works? Here I am pointing to NULL. \nWhy it is allowed? Pointer can take any address, NULL or even invalid address. Still reference to indirection of pointer is allowed?</p>\n<p>Then why it is said \"Reference cannot be null.\" Here, is reference not pointing to <code>NULL</code>?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "27802667", "Title": "Why reference to indirection to pointer is allowed?", "CreationDate": "2015-01-06T16:13:20.607", "Id": "27802605", "CommentCount": "6", "LastEditDate": "2015-01-06T16:23:37.830", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "298661", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-06T16:23:37.830", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "744616", "Tags": "<c++><pointers><reference>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});